{
  "include": [
    "README.mdc",
    ".cursor/rules/**",
    "apps/*/README.mdc",
    "apps/*/.cursor/rules/**"
  ],
  "git": {
    "autoTrackSubmodules": true
  },
  "context": {
    "autoIndexLinkedProjects": true
  }
}

## ðŸ’¡ Notes
- `autoTrackSubmodules: true` keeps all submodules synced with the main repository.
- `autoIndexLinkedProjects: true` allows Cursor to treat submodules as part of the same workspace.
- The context automatically updates when submodules change (e.g. new commits, new files).
- Works best when each submodule also has its own `README.mdc` for local context.

